<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - INSTALL - ROADRANGER
        VALVE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>ROADRANGER VALVE</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>To position the Roadranger valve, the range lever must be to the front or the splitter button to
                    the left when facing forward.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure the nut, valve cover, air lines, sheathing, and O-rings are in position on the
                lever shaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If previously removed, replace the air fittings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020q9">Figure 269</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020q9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020q9" filename="../figg13/G13020q9.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 269. Replace Air Fittings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the Roadranger valve on the lever shaft and rotate into position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020q9">Figure 269</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">From the Roadranger valve bottom, tighten the jam nut (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020q9">Figure 269</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the air lines to the air fittings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020r0">Figure 270</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020r0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020r0" filename="../figg13/G13020r0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 270. Connect Air Lines</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the cover into position on the Roadranger valve (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020r1">Figure 271</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020r1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020r1" filename="../figg13/G13020r1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 271. Roadranger Valve Cover</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the Roadranger valve cover two (2) mounting screws (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020r1">Figure 271</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
